properties.abstract: The granite peaks of the Salbit region are among the best climbing mountains Switzerland has to offer: sharp spires, steep fissures, perfect dièdres, highly structured walls, rough slabs and textbook crags. They can be admired from the hiking area around Meiggelenstock. Moreover, there are two panorama views to enjoy: one into the green gorge of the Reuss valley, the other over to the secluded lakes below Rohrspitzli, which, by the way, deserve an extended visit, too.
properties.subtitle: Surrounded by bold spires
properties.title: From Salbithütte via Meiggelenstock to Wassen

sac_photos.title: One can get wet feet when crossing the Rohrbach in Spring.
A short steep stretch up to Bandlücke
Shortly before the summit; this is the most challenging part of the tour.

segments.description: From Salbithütte the well-marked mountain trail bypasses the lowest point of Seeliboden, gains height quickly on the other side, bypasses some rocky escarpments and leads steeply, but elegantly up to Bandlücke (2357 m). The short detour to the vantage point is well worthwhile. From Bandlücke descend north across granite slabs, branch off at the first opportunity and traverse east across block fields to reach Meiggelenstock on its north ridge. The cross is at around 2370 m.

photos.caption: A short steep stretch up to Bandlücke

segments.title: Salbithütte – Bandlücke – Kreuz

segments.description: Those who still crave a view, scramble up for a few minutes from the cross over rough blocks to the highest point at 2415 m. Back to the cross on the same route.

photos.caption: The block field up to the cross before Meiggelenstock

segments.title: Kreuz - Meiggelenstock - Kreuz

segments.description: From the cross down to P. 2236 and to P. 1939 before the Rohrbach, where the mountain hiking trail to Wassen branches off to the right. Soon steeply through the forest "Bruchwald" down to Wattingen, where we meet the long-distance hiking trail "ViaGotthadro". On it to the left in the Reuss valley to Wassen, bus stop "Dorf".

photos.caption: View from Meiggelenstock down the Reuss valley

segments.title: Kreuz -  Meiggelstock - Bruchwald -  Wassen

segments.description: From Meiggelenstock go back to the bifurcation below Bandlücke and traverse across Rohrplatten to Lang See and Gross See. Then continue to Chli See, and, impressively, to Wildlauenengrat, and through the protective forest of the village you reach Wassen (T3, from Meiggelenstock to Wassen 4 h).

photos.caption: Das Überschreiten des Rohrbachs kann im Frühsommer nasse Füsse geben.
